{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019pu6b3azXsJFQhh2TgCJBf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Cloche System Design\n     2→\n     3→## Overview\n     4→\n     5→Cloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\n     6→environments for coding agents to operate in isolation, a workflow DSL for linking\n     7→agentic and script-driven tasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n     8→\n     9→This document describes the architecture for the MVP (v0.1).\n    10→\n    11→## System Components\n    12→\n    13→Cloche is a Go monorepo producing three binaries:\n    14→\n    15→```\n    16→cmd/\n    17→  cloche/         # CLI client (short-lived)\n    18→  cloched/        # Daemon/orchestrator (long-running)\n    19→  cloche-agent/   # In-container entrypoint (autonomous)\n    20→```\n    21→\n    22→### cloche (CLI)\n    23→\n    24→Short-lived process. Talks to `cloched` over gRPC (Unix socket locally, TCP remotely).\n    25→\n    26→Subcommands:\n    27→- `run <workflow>` — Launch a new workflow run\n    28→- `resume <run-id> [step]` — Resume a failed run from a specific step (or first failed step)\n    29→- `status [run-id]` — Check run status\n    30→- `logs <run-id>` — Stream logs from a running workflow (bidirectional gRPC stream)\n    31→- `stop <run-id>` — Cancel a running workflow (signals container with SIGTERM)\n    32→\n    33→Accepts prompt files or stdin input for user commands.\n    34→\n    35→### cloched (Daemon)\n    36→\n    37→Long-running process. Responsibilities:\n    38→- Launch and manage Docker containers for workflow runs\n    39→- Listen to status streams from running agents\n    40→- Record captures (step inputs, outputs, results, logs)\n    41→- Expose gRPC API for the CLI\n    42→- Persist state via pluggable storage (SQLite initially)\n    43→\n    44→The daemon does NOT interpret workflow logic. It knows \"container X is running workflow Y\"\n    45→and collects status. The agent is self-directing.\n    46→\n    47→### cloche-agent (In-Container Runtime)\n    48→\n    49→Autonomous process running inside the Docker container. Responsibilities:\n    50→- Parse the workflow DSL (workflow files live in the codebase)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6cdefc39-79ad-4cf5-af66-59396d83547b","uuid":"2c55a602-3e1a-4189-ab16-568f714b84bb","timestamp":"2026-03-18T21:57:39.943Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md","content":"# Cloche System Design\n\n## Overview\n\nCloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\nenvironments for coding agents to operate in isolation, a workflow DSL for linking\nagentic and script-driven tasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n\nThis document describes the architecture for the MVP (v0.1).\n\n## System Components\n\nCloche is a Go monorepo producing three binaries:\n\n```\ncmd/\n  cloche/         # CLI client (short-lived)\n  cloched/        # Daemon/orchestrator (long-running)\n  cloche-agent/   # In-container entrypoint (autonomous)\n```\n\n### cloche (CLI)\n\nShort-lived process. Talks to `cloched` over gRPC (Unix socket locally, TCP remotely).\n\nSubcommands:\n- `run <workflow>` — Launch a new workflow run\n- `resume <run-id> [step]` — Resume a failed run from a specific step (or first failed step)\n- `status [run-id]` — Check run status\n- `logs <run-id>` — Stream logs from a running workflow (bidirectional gRPC stream)\n- `stop <run-id>` — Cancel a running workflow (signals container with SIGTERM)\n\nAccepts prompt files or stdin input for user commands.\n\n### cloched (Daemon)\n\nLong-running process. Responsibilities:\n- Launch and manage Docker containers for workflow runs\n- Listen to status streams from running agents\n- Record captures (step inputs, outputs, results, logs)\n- Expose gRPC API for the CLI\n- Persist state via pluggable storage (SQLite initially)\n\nThe daemon does NOT interpret workflow logic. It knows \"container X is running workflow Y\"\nand collects status. The agent is self-directing.\n\n### cloche-agent (In-Container Runtime)\n\nAutonomous process running inside the Docker container. Responsibilities:\n- Parse the workflow DSL (workflow files live in the codebase)","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":253}}}
